By default the `dune` origin reports only the generating dune file. The rule's
dependencies are opt-in. Shown here for the glob-dependent `Generated` module.

  $ generated() {
  >   dune describe workspace --lang 0.1 --sanitize-for-tests "$@" \
  >     | censor | sed -n '/(name Generated)/,/(name Mylib)/p' | sed '$d'
  > }

`--with-origin-deps` adds the rule's dependencies as declared (a glob stays a
glob):

  $ generated --with-origin-deps
       ((name Generated)
        (impl (_build/default/generated.ml))
        (intf ())
        (cmt (_build/default/.mylib.objs/byte/mylib__Generated.cmt))
        (cmti ())
        (origin
         (dune
          ((dune_file dune)
           (deps
            ((File_selector
              ((dir (In_build_dir default))
               (predicate (Element (Glob *.txt)))
               (only_generated_files false)))))))))

`--with-origin-deps-expanded` adds them expanded to the concrete matching files:

  $ generated --with-origin-deps-expanded
       ((name Generated)
        (impl (_build/default/generated.ml))
        (intf ())
        (cmt (_build/default/.mylib.objs/byte/mylib__Generated.cmt))
        (cmti ())
        (origin
         (dune
          ((dune_file dune)
           (expanded_deps
            ((In_build_dir default/dep.txt)
             (In_build_dir default/extra.txt)))))))

Both flags together report the dependencies in both forms:

  $ generated --with-origin-deps --with-origin-deps-expanded
       ((name Generated)
        (impl (_build/default/generated.ml))
        (intf ())
        (cmt (_build/default/.mylib.objs/byte/mylib__Generated.cmt))
        (cmti ())
        (origin
         (dune
          ((dune_file dune)
           (deps
            ((File_selector
              ((dir (In_build_dir default))
               (predicate (Element (Glob *.txt)))
               (only_generated_files false)))))
           (expanded_deps
            ((In_build_dir default/dep.txt)
             (In_build_dir default/extra.txt)))))))
